  <!-- LOCAL KNOWLEDGE -->
  <section class="local-section" id="local">
    <h2>Chimney Sweeping in Officer</h2>
    <div class="local-box"><p>Officer is a rapidly growing outer south-eastern suburb in the City of Casey that has expanded dramatically since the mid-2000s, transforming from a small rural area into a major residential growth corridor. The suburb sits at the point where Melbourne's south-eastern urban edge meets the Cardinia Hills to the north-east, and its exposed Cardinia plain position means it experiences some of the coldest winter conditions on the metropolitan fringe. The housing stock in Officer is almost entirely estate housing from the 2000s onward — large four and five bedroom homes in planned residential estates where slow combustion wood heaters were specified as the primary supplementary heating system in a significant proportion of builds. These newer estate homes face a genuine winter heating challenge: the flat, open plain around Officer is exposed to cold southerly and south-westerly airflows that push temperatures well below Melbourne's urban average, and the combination of a large family home and proper cold weather makes the slow combustion heater essential rather than optional. Many of Officer's heaters are reaching the point where they have been in consistent use for several winters but have never received a professional flue clean — the stage at which creosote accumulation becomes both a fire risk and a performance issue. We service Officer and the Cardinia corridor regularly and are familiar with the estate-home slow combustion configurations common throughout the suburb.</p></div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="signs-section" id="signs">
    <h2>Signs Your Officer Chimney Needs Cleaning</h2>
    <ul class="signs-list">
      <li>Slow combustion heater backing smoke into the room — especially at startup</li>
      <li>Sluggish draw that makes the heater difficult to light and maintain</li>
      <li>An acrid or smoky smell in the house after the heater runs</li>
      <li>Tar deposits visible on the external flue sections or ceiling plate</li>
      <li>A heater that was installed new when the home was built and has never been serviced</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <!-- SERVICES -->
  <section class="services-section" id="services">
    <h2>Chimney Services in Officer</h2>
    <div class="services-grid">
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Chimney Sweep</h3><p>Full brush sweep from firebox to pot. Soot, creosote and debris removed. Verbal condition report included.</p></div>
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Flue Cleaning</h3><p>Thorough flue clean using professional brushes and equipment. Removes accumulated creosote and restores full draw.</p></div>
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Wood Heater Service</h3><p>Slow combustion heater flue clean and inspection. Baffle check, door seal inspection, full flue swept top to bottom.</p></div>
      <div class="service-card"><h3>Chimney Inspection</h3><p>Visual inspection of firebox, flue, damper, crown and pot. Written report available on request. Included in the $199 service.</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- REVIEWS -->
  <section class="reviews-section" id="reviews">
    <h2>What Officer Customers Say</h2>
    <div class="reviews-grid">
      <div class="review-card"><div class="review-stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div><p class="review-text">&ldquo;Brand new estate home in Officer South and the heater had been in for five winters. David cleaned the flue and said the creosote build-up was worse than he'd expect for the age. Will be booking annually from now on.&rdquo;</p><p class="review-author">Brad S., Officer</p></div>
      <div class="review-card"><div class="review-stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div><p class="review-text">&ldquo;David was prompt, professional and very clear about what he found. Cleaned the full flue and gave us a condition report we could actually understand. Great service — highly recommend.&rdquo;</p><p class="review-author">Tracey H., Officer</p></div>
      <div class="review-card"><div class="review-stars">&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;&#9733;</div><p class="review-text">&ldquo;Heater had been running poorly for a season. David found the flue was significantly restricted. After the clean the draw improved immediately. Wish we had called sooner — very professional.&rdquo;</p><p class="review-author">Chris P., Officer</p></div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ABOUT -->
